<subSubSection id="E995AFFBFFC8981DF7FB2B29F9CCFB4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2B29F788FD4E" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• Largest terrestrial mammals with stout body, characteristic long, highly dexterous proboscis extended from upper lip, large ears, column-like limbs, and small tail.</paragraph>
<caption id="F5F0ACF8FFC8981DF7FB2BBBFA0CFD67" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6511088" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6511088" box="[1266,1483,711,744]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6511088/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="50" targetBox="[1483,2025,746,933]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2BBBFA0CFD67" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" box="[1266,1483,711,744]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• 670-900 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="F5F0ACF8FFC8981DF7FB2ACFF8BEFC5B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6511092" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6511092" box="[1266,1913,947,980]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6511092/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="50" targetBox="[254,1202,598,1229]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2ACFF8BEFC5B" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" box="[1266,1913,947,980]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• Afrotropical and Indo-Malayan Regions.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2AA2FA78FBC5" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• All major habitats in Africa, including tropical forest, woodland, savanna, and desert; primarily wooded habitats in Asia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2D29F961FBFD" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" box="[1266,1702,1109,1138]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• 2 genera, 3 species, 3 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A130FC70FFC8981DF7FB2D04F9CCFB4F" blockId="0.[1264,2146,597,1218]" pageId="0" pageNumber="50">• 2 species Endangered, 1 species Vulnerable; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
